author: CNN
description: On the verge of retirement, Mitch McConnell faces a surprising turn: the Republicans vying to replace him are attacking his legacy. Kentucky’s leading GOP Senate candidates, all former McConnell interns, once called him a mentor but are now racing to disavow him amid Trump’s grip on the party.   #CNN #News
title: McConnell's Former Interns Now Opponents in Senate Race

author: CNN
description: In a press conference, President Donald Trump said he "will not allow" Israel to annex the West Bank.
title: Trump says he 'will not allow Israel to annex the West Bank'

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump signed an executive order clearing the way for the completion of a deal to sell TikTok’s US assets to a consortium of mostly American investors. Reporters asked the president if he would like to see the new algorithm suggest more MAGA-related content. #CNN #News
title: Reporter asks Trump about MAGA-leaning algorithm after new TikTok order

author: CNN
description: Nearly eight months after the deadly midair collision near Washington’s Reagan National Airport, the widow of passenger Casey Crafton has filed the first federal lawsuit. She is suing American Airlines and the US government, alleging wrongful death and negligence. CNN correspondent Brian Todd joins Wolf Blitzer in the Situation Room.   #CNN #News
title: Widow brings first federal suit in DC midair collision

author: CNN
description: Tropical Storm Humberto could reach major hurricane status this weekend -- but the bigger threat to the US is a storm that hasn't formed yet. Tropical Storm Imelda is expected to develop in the coming days and could impact the Southeast US early next week. But there's still a lot of uncertainty and many factors at play -- including an interaction with Humberto. #cnn #news
title: Interacting storms could result in US landfall

author: CNN
description: The US Food and Drug Administration is reviewing evidence about the safety and efficacy of mifepristone, a drug commonly used in medication abortions. The review is driving new concerns about limits on access. CNN’s Meg Tirrell reports. #cnn #news #rfkjr #fda #mifepristone
title: FDA reviewing safety of the abortion pill mifepristone, sparking concerns about access

author: CNN
description: Multiple airports in Denmark were disrupted by drones this week in what the government describes as a “hybrid attack” by unidentified professional actors. The incidents have prompted consideration of invoking NATO’s Article 4 for the first time. Danish authorities suggest a possible link to recent alleged Russian drone violations of NATO airspace in Poland and Romania. Russia’s embassy in Denmark denied any involvement, calling the speculation “absurd.”   #CNN #News
title: Drones shut down Danish airports in ‘hybrid attack,’ say officials

author: CNN
description: Katie Couric spoofed Sydney Sweeney's controversial denim ad to draw attention to colon cancer awareness.
title: See how Katie Couric flipped the script on Sweeney’s controversial ad

author: CNN
description: Andrzej Bargiel has just become the first person to climb up and ski down Mt. Everest without bottled oxygen, according to RedBull.
title: He just became the first to ski down Everest without bottled oxygen

author: CNN
description: A senior White House official told reporters Monday that TikTok’s US algorithm will be managed by Oracle as part of the proposed sale to a majority-American ownership group. The deal would shift control of US operations and the algorithm to a US-based joint venture.   #CNN #News
title: TikTok algorithm in the US to be managed by Oracle

author: CNN
description: As the government funding deadline looms over Capitol Hill, CNN’s Manu Raju describes why Democrats have leverage ahead of a potential shutdown, and how Republicans are looking to push back. #cnn #news #politics
title: Why Democrats have leverage in the government shutdown fight

author: CNN
description: The White House budget office is instructing federal agencies to prepare for mass firings if a government shutdown occurs, an apparent threat by the Trump administration amid a standoff with congressional Democrats over federal funding. The directive, detailed in an OMB memo obtained by CNN, marks a departure from past shutdown practices.   #CNN #News
title: White House warns of mass federal layoffs if government shuts down

author: CNN
description: US President Donald Trump spoke about Russia and its president Vladimir Putin during his meeting with Turkish President Tayyip Erdoğan at the White House, telling reporters he was “very disappointed in Putin” for prolonging the war. #cnn #news
title: Trump says he's 'very disappointed' in Putin for prolonging war

author: CNN
description: Jeremy Carl, a top Trump State Department nominee, deleted thousands of social media posts, many demonstrating a history of inflammatory commentary— including incendiary posts about race, claims that “peaceful coexistence” with Democrats is impossible, and even a call for a political opponent to face the death penalty. CNN's Andrew Kaczynski reports. #CNN #News
title: Trump official deleted thousands of posts

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump suggested that Israel and Hamas are “close to getting some kind of a deal done.” The president spoke with reporters during his bilateral meeting with Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan at the White House.
title: Trump says ‘close to getting some kind of a deal’ on ceasefire

author: CNN
description: Authorities have identified the suspect in the ICE detention center shooting in Dallas as 29-year-old Joshua John. The FBI says he fired from a rooftop, striking the building and vehicles on site. One detainee was killed, two others critically injured. FBI Director Kash Patel shared photos of bullet casings, including one inscribed “anti-ICE.” For more perspective, CNN's Wolf Blitzer is joined by former ICE Director Sarah Saldaña.   #CNN #News
title: DHS steps up protections at immigration centers after shooting

author: CNN
description:
Charlie Kirk's organization, Turning Point USA, continued its national tour of college campuses with a stop at Virginia Tech ahead of pivotal elections in the state. Conservative media pundit Megyn Kelly got into a heated exchange with an attendee over political violence.

#cnn #news #virginia #virginiatech #megynkelly #turningpointusa #trump
title: Megyn Kelly gets into heated exchange at Turning Point USA event

author: CNN
description: Harvard University was the first to take the fight over US government influence on college campuses to court, and the nation’s oldest, richest university is still fighting. CNN’s Omar Jimenez reports in "The United States VS Harvard" on "The Whole Story with Anderson Cooper" on September 28 at 10pm ET/PT.      #CNN   #News  #TheWholeStory
title: The Fight Between the US Government and Harvard

author: CNN
description: Senate Majority Leader John Thune (R-SD), tells CNN's Dana Bash he believes the FCC should not use its power "in a coercive way when it comes to the First Amendment." Thune was asked whether FCC Chairman Brendan Carr and US President Donald Trump "went too far" with late night host Jimmy Kimmel. #cnn #news #johnthune #danabash #shorts
title: Sen. Majority Leader: FCC power shouldn’t be ‘used in coercive way’

author: CNN
description:
Jimmy Kimmel returned to TV after being suspended for his comments on Charlie Kirk's assassination. It was the latest sign of political pressure shaping the media landscape into something that may have been unrecognizable a decade ago. Axios media correspondent and CNN contributor Sara Fischer talks about the forces at play and how they’re influencing everything from talk shows to social media algorithms.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tawacyt092525

#cnn #news #media #tv #socialmedia #politics #jimmykimmel #kimmel #fcc
title: How MAGA is reshaping what you watch and read | The Assignment

author: CNN
description: A Paris court sentenced former French President Nicolas Sarkozy to 5 years in prison, even if he appeals, after finding him guilty in his trial for alleged illegal campaign funding from former Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi.
title: Former French President Sarkozy will go to prison

author: CNN
description: In August, the Integrated Food Security Phase Classification confirmed that a famine is taking place in Gaza, but there had already been hundreds of hunger and malnutrition related deaths before then. CNN looks at why the classification took so long when alarm bells had been ringing months in advance. #cnn #news
title: Famine in Gaza was declared last month. Why did it come so late?

author: CNN
description: In a post on Truth Social, President Donald Trump blasted the United Nations over what he described as a “triple sabotage,” citing an escalator breakdown, teleprompter malfunction, and audio problems that he claimed were part of a coordinated effort to disrupt his appearance.  #CNN #News
title: Trump calls for probe into alleged ‘triple sabotage’ at UN

author: CNN
description: In an interview with CNN's Christiane Amanpour on the sidelines of the UN General Assembly in New York, President of the EU commission Ursula von der Leyen says that NATO must defend itself in response to recent incursions into its airspace. #cnn #news
title: EU Chief warns NATO to defend itself

author: CNN
description: Five-year-old Tim Hryshchuk shows CNN the bomb shelter in his school basement in Kyiv. Daily life in Ukraine has been rocked by Russia's daytime bombardment of its cities, making shelters a necessity.
title: This is what a bomb shelter looks like at a Ukrainian school

author: CNN
description: The NewsNight panel debated the new "Presidential Walk of Fame" with photos of the presidents in order. There is one exception, Joe Biden's photo is not of the former President, it's an image of his autopen. Adam Mockler from MeidasTouch has an idea for how the next president should change the photos. #CNN #News
title: Panelist: I hope next Dem president posts pics of Trump and Epstein at White House

author: CNN
description: Danish Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen has apologized to women in Greenland over the use of forced contraception. Thousands of women young girls were fitted with intrauterine devices without their knowledge or consent while Denmark was in charge of Greenland's healthcare system for 25 years. #cnn #greenland #denmark
title: Danish PM apologizes to Greenland women for forced birth control

author: CNN
description: An airport in northern Denmark was forced to close when unauthorized drones entered its airspace, police said. This is the second drone-caused closure at a Danish airport this week. #CNN #News
title: Flying object seen at Danish airport

author: CNN
description: Lifelong Republican Sheryl Underwood has praised Jimmy Kimmel's comeback, saying his return to air showed "more grace and more humanity than all the people that are involved." Speaking to CNN, Underwood called for Christians to forgive mistakes. #cnn #jimmykimmel #jimmykimmelshow
title: Republican talk show host Sheryl Underwood praises Jimmy Kimmel

author: CNN
description: Vice President JD Vance criticized Jimmy Kimmel on Wednesday in an interview on NewsNation, saying the late-night host failed to apologize during his return to television following backlash over comments made after the death of conservative activist Charlie Kirk. #CNN #News
title: JD Vance says Kimmel ‘didn’t actually say sorry’ to Kirk

author: CNN
description: The Metropolitan Transportation Authority took to Instagram to announce that rapper Cardi B will voice PSAs that play in subway stations across New York City. #cnn #news #MTA #cardib #NYC
title: Cardi B to voice new subway PSAs

author: CNN
description: Former California Republican Governor Arnold Schwarzenegger is calling for bipartisan action on climate change.
title: Hear what issue Schwarzenegger says was a dealbreaker for support of Trump

author: CNN
description: ABC and Disney face potential backlash from President Trump after reinstating Jimmy Kimmel’s show, which Trump criticized on social media. Kimmel's return following a suspension over comments about Charlie Kirk’s suspected killer averaged 6.3 million viewers via traditional television and reached tens of millions of people online. Some affiliates, including Sinclair and Nexstar, did not air the episode, meaning their audiences missed Kimmel’s emotional remarks to Charlie Kirk supporters.   #CNN #News
title: Trump lashes out at ABC over Kimmel’s return

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Jim Sciutto shares his takeaways from the UN General Assembly so far.
title: Takeaways from the UN General Assembly
